definitions.definition: The "false" ( singing ) voice in any human , usually airy and lacking a purity of vowels; created by using the next highest vocal folds above those used for speech and normal range singing. It is commonly confused with the head voice register.
A person who sings in falsetto.

main_definition: ( singing , uncountable ) The "false" ( singing ) voice in any human , usually airy and lacking a purity of vowels; created by using the next highest vocal folds above those used for speech and normal range singing. It is commonly confused with the head voice register.
secondary_definitions: ( music , countable ) A person who sings in falsetto.
